Let \Bbbk  / \mathbb {F} be an extension, let \alpha _{1},…,\alpha _{r}\in \Bbbk . Define the extensions
\mathbb {F}=F_{0}\subseteq  F_{1}\subseteq …\subseteq  F_{r}
by F_{i+1}=F_{i}(\alpha _{i+1}). Then F_{r}=\mathbb {F}(\alpha _{1},…,\alpha _{r}).

